                <note type="abstract">Additional fragments have been published/announced in (Hopkins)

The author posits the early non-Saadianic (i.e., pre-10th-century) provenance—based on its “hebraized spelling”—of a two-leaf fragment in the Taylor-Schechter Collection containing Judaeo-Arabic translation (in Hebrew-script) of Prov 16:24–17:26. The possibility of this fragment’s Qaraite provenance is raised on p. 32, n. 10 (on which, inter alia, see further the 2000 article of Blau and Hopkins in Pe‘amim). An edition and English translation of the fragment is included.</note>
